Portugal is set to build the world's largest solar energy power station in Moura, with 350,000 solar panels producing 62 megawatts.
The project, overseen by Amper Central Solar, aims to create 240 jobs in the Alentejo region.
Meanwhile, a Dutch team won a solar-powered car race in Australia, showcasing the potential of solar energy.
In the Philippines, a solar power project will benefit rural households and provide essential services.
Taiwan is also making strides in solar energy development, aiming to become a top global player by 2008.
